body.body: Service Bulletin 598 - Rear Bevel Box Breather
Dealers are requested to remove the rear bevel box breather and refit with sealant as described in the procedure below.
Motorcycles in the affected VIN range must be modified prior to delivery to the customer, or at the next visit to the dealership.
Tiger 1200 GT, Tiger 1200 GT Pro, Tiger 1200 Rally Pro, Tiger 1200 GT Explorer and Tiger 1200 Rally Explorer motorcycles in the above VIN range.
Service Bulletin - Note - Identification of Affected Motorcycles
Some affected motorcycles listed in the VIN range will have been modified and repaired by Triumph prior to their release from the factory.
Unmodified motorcycles can be identified by checking the ‘VIN Enquiry’ on www.triumphonline.net.
Service Bulletin - Parts Ordering Instructions - Not Applicable
Service Bulletin - Genuine Parts Return Instructions - Not Applicable
Once completed, please mark the Service Record Book that the requirements of this bulletin have been complied with.
Before returning the motorcycle to the customer, download the latest calibration using the current version of the Triumph diagnostic software to the following:
Rear Bevel Box Breather Removal and Installation
Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.
A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.
An unstable motorcycle may fall, causing injury to the operator or damage to the motorcycle.
Remove the rear bevel box breather from the rear bevel box, noting the position of the locating tang for installation.
Make sure the rear bevel box breather is clean and free of debris.

Apply Threebond 1216E sealant (or equivalent if not available in market) to the entire circumference in the area shown below. The sealant must not pass the apex of the bead as highlighted by the dotted line on the illustration.

body.name: Rear Bevel Box Breather Sealant PV SB598

body.body: Sealant not to cross this line
Install the rear bevel box breather to the rear bevel box with the locating tang positioned as noted during removal.
Circulation Box - use inside bulletin structure
Initial and date when read and return to central file holder
